<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY WILL OFFER INFLUENZA SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego County Public Health Services will offer influenza immunizations at 
special clinics in November, a spokesman said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The immunization program, conducted out of the county's seven public health 
centers, is available to people 55 and older, and other risk groups susceptible 
to contracting the flu, the spokesman said. The county Department of Health 
Services also recommends immunization for people who live with high-risk group 
members. 
</P>
<P>
The fee for shots is $2 but can be waived if a person can't afford it. For more 
information, call the 24-hour information line at 236-2350. In North County, 
the number is 940-1462. 
</P>
</TEXT>
