<HEADLINE>
<P>
'IGNORANCE IS NO BLISS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your editorial suggests that teaching core cultural subjects should begin 
before college. You are right, of course. However, you don't go far enough. 
</P>
<P>
Children spend much more time watching TV than they do in school. We seem to 
forget the lessons that the success of "Sesame Street" taught us. Very young 
children love to learn from that program. Public broadcasting should be 
adequately funded to operate without corporate support and without having to 
beg for private donations. The amount of funding each station receives should 
provide incentives based on educational success. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD FOY 
</P>
<P>
Redondo Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
