<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL CROSS-COUNTRY ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MCCRANK'S FINISH NUDGES HART INTO FIRST PLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Hart High boys' cross-country team, second-ranked in the Southern Section 
3-A Division, tied No. 1 San Gabriel, 28-28, Thursday at San Gabriel High, but 
won the Foothill League meet because its sixth runner posted a faster time than 
San Gabriel's fifth runner. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Steve McCrank, the Indians' sixth runner, placed 10th in 16:37. McCrank 
finished ahead of Dorro Pingarron, San Gabriel's fifth and final scorer. 
</P>
<P>
"He's the hero," Hart Coach Gene Blankenship said. "He's getting better every 
week." 
</P>
<P>
The victory moved Hart (5-0 in league meets) into first place and gives the 
Indians at least a share of the league dual-meet championship for the seventh 
consecutive season. San Gabriel (4-1) dropped to second place. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Lepken (15:38) and Hector Chavez (15:52) paced Hart with second- and 
fourth-place finishes. 
</P>
<P>
Angel Martinez timed 15:15 to lead the Matadors. 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' meets: 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 26, Grant 29 -- The Huskies captured the East Valley League 
title with the win at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
Dov Waisman (16:38) and David Mazin (17:37) placed first and second for North 
Hollywood (3-0 in league) 
</P>
<P>
Grant dropped to 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 24, Kennedy 31 -- San Fernando (3-0) sewed up the North Valley 
League title at Pierce College. The Tigers' Obed Aguirre finished first in a 
personal-best 15 minutes, 11 seconds over the three-mile course. 
</P>
<P>
The Golden Cougars (2-1) were led by Warren Reich, who finished second in 
16:18. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 24, Kennedy 33 -- San Fernando snapped Kennedy's winning streak of 
49 league dual meets with the upset at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
Aracely Flores (20:54) of Kennedy (2-1) finished first but the Tigers placed 
three runners in the top five finishers to clinch the league title. 
</P>
<P>
Julie Hernandez (22:11) and Maria Sanchez (22:22) paced San Fernando (3-0) with 
second- and third-place finishes. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 27, Notre Dame 30 -- The sixth-ranked Guards (7-1, 5-1) survived 
first- and second-place finishes by Notre Dame to win a San Fernando Valley 
League meet at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame senior Lynn Hosek finished first in a school-record time 18:41 to 
lead the Knights (4-3, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 23, Grant 34 -- Rosa Melendez finished first in 19:42 to pace 
North Hollywood (3-0) to the East Valley League title at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
Mari Chernow (21:35) and Rachel Gibson (21:53) placed second and third for the 
Lancers (1-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
