ARRESTED HART PLAYERS TO PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDAN HEALEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five Hart High varsity football players arrested Tuesday for allegedly 
kidnaping a 17-year-old girl will not face disciplinary action from the school, 
Hart Athletic Director Bill Beauer said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"We don't have any jurisdiction," Beauer said. "It has nothing to do with the 
school. . . . What they do after hours on their own time is not our business." 
</P>
<P>
Beauer said that all five players will be allowed to play in Hart's game 
tonight against Burbank. The players were released into their parents' custody 
after the arrests. 
</P>
<P>
The alleged kidnaping occurred early Saturday and appeared to be a prank, a 
police spokesman said. The boys forced the girl, a schoolmate, into a van and 
left her on Pico Canyon Road. Walking out of the canyon, the girl once more was 
forced into the van, then was taken to a friend's home in Newhall. BRENDAN 
HEALEY 
