<P>
EXTRA $3.2 BILLION FOR DRUG WAR URGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
House and Senate negotiators agreed to provide $3.2 billion this year to beef 
up the Bush Administration's war on drugs and other crime-fighting ventures. 
The money represents the major congressional role in the war on drugs this 
year. Despite the aura of urgency surrounding the issue, lawmakers had taken no 
action on the funding since the Senate approved it a month ago. The decision by 
a House and Senate conference committee got the money moving again and brought 
total funding for the drug war to $8.8 billion. 
</P>
