<SUBJECT>
<P>
CONTRACTS; BASKETBALL PLAYERS -- WAGES AND SALARIES; SACRAMENTO KINGS 
(BASKETBALL TEAM); ELLISON, PERVIS; TISDALE, WAYMAN 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102789-0092 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 126473 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 27, 1989, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 7; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
87 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Moore, a former starting offensive lineman for the New England Patriots, 
was shot and killed after apparently being robbed outside a convenience store 
in Memphis, Tenn., Wednesday night, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Moore, 29, a tackle for the Patriots from 1983 through 1987, bought several 
items at the store and then was shot as he returned to his car, Lt. Hank Arnold 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Moore managed to get back inside the store and told the clerk he had been 
robbed and shot. 
</P>
<P>
There were no witnesses, and police have no suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
