<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SLAIN WOMAN'S BODY FOUND IN GRIFFITH PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a Los Angeles woman was found dumped beside a curb early Thursday 
in Griffith Park less than an hour after the woman was hit on the head and 
killed, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
A man driving home from work alerted park rangers when he spotted the 
38-year-old woman's nude body about 4:30 a.m. on Zoo Drive east of Victory 
Boulevard, Detective Sam Jacobellis said. Authorities declined to identify the 
woman until next of kin were notified. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators, who have not established a motive or list of suspects, said they 
believe the woman died about 4 a.m. of a blow to the head. 
</P>
<P>
Police identified the woman through fingerprints. 
</P>
</TEXT>
