<P>
ELUSIVE CITY KITTY CAUGHT, INCARCERATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a daylong attempt Thursday, Newport Beach finally bagged its cat. 
</P>
<P>
An animal control supervisor got hold of the small cat believed to be the one 
that got stuck Wednesday between the walls of City Hall, Police Sgt. Andy Gonis 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Elusive to the end, the cat avoided a trap set for it and was eventually 
cornered by animal control supervisor Bill Lyons. 
</P>
<P>
Gonis said the cat was taken to the city pound, where it will remain while 
animal control workers will try to find its owner. 
</P>
