<P>
127 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO WILL TRY TO RECOVER AGAINST GOLDEN WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Santiago College is hoping to rebound and Golden West is looking for an 
upset in a Mission Conference Central Division football game at 7 tonight at 
Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago opened the season with five victories but was defeated by 
Riverside, 34-24, last Saturday. The Dons are 5-1 overall, 4-1 in conference 
play and 0-1 in the division. 
</P>
<P>
The Dons were ranked sixth in the national J.C. Grid-Wire poll before the loss, 
but now are 19th. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West (3-2, 2-2, 0-1) is going for its third Friday night victory of the 
season. Games are normally played on Saturday, but due to scheduling conflicts 
created because Golden West shares a field with Orange Coast, the Rustlers 
already have played -- and won -- twice on Friday this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102789-0160 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 126643 </DOCID>
