<P>
LENDL, SOUTHLAND'S CHANG IN ANTWERP SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANTWERP, Belgium 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Ivan Lendl and Placentia teen-ager Michael Chang scored straight-set 
victories today to set up a semifinal match in the $1-million Community 
Championship. 
</P>
<P>
Lendl defeated Austrian Horst Skoff 6-3, 6-3, and Chang ousted Alberto Mancini 
of Argentina 6-4, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Their meeting in the semifinal will be their first since Chang defeated the 
world's No. 1 player on his way to the French Open title. 
</P>
